page.title: 20LIVING CREATURES
page.content: As this is a rural area, the land is heavily populated with a variety of wild animals seen by local residents. {Mammals:}Badgers, Foxes, Hares, Rabbits, Grey Squirrels, a rare Red Squirrel has been seen, Rats,Shrews, Fieldmice, Dormice, Harvest Mice, Moles, Voles, Water Rats & Voles, Hedgehogs, Stoats & Weasels, Bats. {Birds:}Pheasant, Partridge, Duck, Wood Pigeons, Asiatic Collar Doves,Magpies, Swallows, Swifts, House Martins, Cuckoos, Curlew, Green & Spotted Wood- peckers, Tree Creeper, Kestrels, Nut- hatch, Wagtails, Yellow Hammer, Little & Barn Owls, Sparrows, Robins, Wrens, Chaffinch, Bullfinch, Lapwings, Kingfisher. {Butterflies:}Common Blue, Wall, Paint- ed Lady, Peacock, Cabbage White, Orange Tip, Red Admiral, Tortoiseshell Brimstone Yellow.
